The paper deals with digital image sampling and recovery, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and information theory (cs.IT). The proposed method also involves using adaptive and intelligent techniques, which could be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and signal processing (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the proposed framework, which could be considered under computer graphics (cs.GR) and computer systems and networking (cs.SI).
